@startuml uc5_list_part_1
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title UC-05 Part 1: Projects List View và Filtering

actor "Marketing\nAnalyst" as User
participant "Web UI\n(Next.js)" as UI
participant "Project Service\n(Golang)" as ProjectSvc
database "PostgreSQL\n(projects table)" as DB

== Initial Page Load ==

User -> UI: Navigate to "/projects"\n(from menu or after login)
activate UI

UI -> ProjectSvc: GET /api/v1/projects\nAuthorization: Bearer <JWT>
activate ProjectSvc

ProjectSvc -> ProjectSvc: Verify JWT\nExtract user_id

ProjectSvc -> DB: SELECT * FROM projects\nWHERE created_by = :user_id\n  AND deleted_at IS NULL\nORDER BY created_at DESC\nLIMIT 20 OFFSET 0
activate DB

DB --> ProjectSvc: Return projects list:\n[\n  {id, name, status, created_at,\n   brand_keywords_preview: [...3 keywords]}\n]
deactivate DB

ProjectSvc --> UI: 200 OK\n{\n  "projects": [...],\n  "total": 45,\n  "page": 1\n}
deactivate ProjectSvc

UI -> UI: Render Projects List:\n- Cards với name, status badge\n- Created date, last updated\n- Brand keywords preview

UI --> User: Display Projects page\nwith filter controls
deactivate UI

== Apply Filters ==

User -> UI: Apply filters:\n- Status: "completed"\n- Search: "brand A"\n- Sort: "created_at DESC"
activate UI

UI -> ProjectSvc: GET /api/v1/projects?\nstatus=completed&\nsearch=brand%20A&\nsort=created_at&\norder=desc
activate ProjectSvc

ProjectSvc -> DB: SELECT * FROM projects\nWHERE created_by = :user_id\n  AND deleted_at IS NULL\n  AND status = 'completed'\n  AND name ILIKE '%brand A%'\nORDER BY created_at DESC\nLIMIT 20
activate DB

DB --> ProjectSvc: Return filtered list:\n[...12 matching projects]
deactivate DB

ProjectSvc --> UI: 200 OK\n{\n  "projects": [...12],\n  "total": 12,\n  "filters_applied": {...}\n}
deactivate ProjectSvc

UI -> UI: Update display:\n"Showing 12 of 45 projects"

UI --> User: Display filtered results
deactivate UI

== Pagination (Optional) ==

note over User, DB
  If user has > 50 projects,\n  pagination activates with\n  20 items/page + infinite scroll
end note

User -> UI: Scroll to bottom
activate UI

UI -> ProjectSvc: GET /api/v1/projects?\npage=2&limit=20
activate ProjectSvc

ProjectSvc -> DB: SELECT ... OFFSET 20 LIMIT 20
activate DB
DB --> ProjectSvc: Next 20 items
deactivate DB

ProjectSvc --> UI: 200 OK with next page
deactivate ProjectSvc

UI -> UI: Append to list\n(infinite scroll)

UI --> User: Load more projects
deactivate UI

@enduml
